Fertiliser Producers and Suppliers Association of Nigeria (FEPSAN) yesterday commenced a 2-day capacity building workshop for stakeholders from 31 fertiliser blending companies across the country. Addressing participants in his
welcome remark, FEPSAN executive secretary, Mr. Gideon Negedu said the
capacity building for all fertiliser blending plants across the
country was basically to upgrade their knowledge on fertiliser
blending formulation that will meet the test of time. Represented by administration officer of FEPSAN, Faiza Abdulsalam,  the
executive secretary  said FEPSAN has continued to strive to ensure the
growth of the fertiliser industry in Nigeria. He added that FEPSAN focus has been to have a growth that is inclusive
of all stakeholders in the fertiliser supply chain, from government
that provides regulations and an enabling environment, producers and
blenders of fertiliser to distributors and of course the farmers that
use the product. “The main objective of this capacity building are to develop and
deliver capacity building for blending plants on new fertiliser
blends, deepen advocacy on crop and site specific blends and catalyze
the production of appropriate crop and sites specific fertiliser
blends. “The need for blending soil specific fertiliser can never be
overlooked and our goal and objectives as a body and as a main
shareholder in the fertiliser industry is to make sure that the right
quality of fertiliser gets to the end user at the appropriate time. “Therefore, the fertiliser bill has in recent time, addressed issues of adulteration, use of
inappropriate machineries, tools
and racketeering in which culprits are getting to know that they will
face the wrath of the law if found wanting”.